    <h3>Steffi</h3>
    <p>Today we both woke up with stuffy noses, and I also got a sore throat. Great, the timing couldn't be better. We were planning to visit the "Otway Fly Treetop Walk" today!</p>
    <p>Since Basti had his Merlin card and I had the voucher from our win in the monopoly game at a fast food chain, we both had free admission! We started exploring the first section of the forest until we came to the "scaffolding" that would take us to dizzying heights. However, there wasn't much to see. After a while, we came across a viewing tower.</p>
    <p>While Basti stayed below because our breathing was somewhat restricted due to our colds, I decided to conquer the viewing tower and went up alone. After what felt like an eternity and many breaks on the way up, I again met the German family that we kept running into during the tour, and they agreed to take a photo of me up there.</p>
    <p>Unfortunately, the view left a lot to be desired. The trees had grown so tall that you couldn't actually see anything! I went back down after a few minutes, and we continued the tour. However, it didn't get any more exciting.</p>
    <p>Conclusion: The regular admission price we would have had to pay wouldn't have been justified. But as a free diversion, it was nice!</p>
