    <p>On the way back, we decided to take a different route, which led us along a very narrow road with trees and rock walls on both sides. How fortunate that there isn't much oncoming traffic in this remote area!</p>
    <p>By then it was lunchtime, and hunger drove us into town. We parked Hugo back at the tourist information center and set out on foot. Unfortunately, we ran into the familiar problem again:</p>
    <p><em>"Basti and Steffi are hungry, but all shops are closed."</em></p>
    <p>So we first went to the supermarket to stock up on tissues, which were completely overpriced, and eucalyptus oil before returning to the campsite to cook something. After the meal, we visited the campsite pool, where Basti first turned it into a full eucalyptus bath, while I made myself comfortable with a book.</p>
    <p>Thanks to the bacteria, we didn't have much energy today, so we went to bed early to be ready for the next day. Good night.</p>
